The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 In celebration of Odissi

 In celebration of its second anniversary, Sankalpa Nrityayan, dedicated to the promotion of Odissi as a classical art form, presents an evening of this classical dance by members of its troupe. Also, felicitation to the celebrated Odissi exponent, Padma Shri Kumkum Mohanty, and Chuni Goswami, sheriff of Calcutta. The latter part of the concert features Tuhu Mama Madhava, a dance-drama based on the Vaishnav Padavali. A compilation of lyrical compositions dealing with the passionate love of Radha and Krishna, it begins by portraying Radha?s jealousy and depression on learning of Krishna?s dalliance with Chandraboli. Radha accuses Krishna of betraying her love when he arrives at the break of dawn. Ultimately, the two lovers are reunited after Krishna seeks forgiveness. The choreographic presentation culminates with a grand celebration of their union by the sakhis.

 Event: An evening of Odissi dance presented by Sankalpa Nrityayan

 When: Today at 6 pm

 Where: Gyan Manch




